item.title: Hepialidae spp.
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: On wet, warmish autumn nights we get hundreds of rain moths - 17 on this window pane. Mostly O. dirempta/lyelli but occasional O. antipoda (or australis) and T. atripalpis. Tawny Frogmouths feast on them.

item.title: Chrysolarentia correlata
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Distinctly yellow in flight and on landing. Gives a few wing flaps on landing before resting. This species might merge with C. insulsata (see CD that comes with Moths of Victoria 3). New species record for Riddells Creek.

item.title: Aenetus ligniveren
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Found dead on the garden path this morning. Apparently males are rarely seen. New species record for Riddells Creek.

item.title: Taxeotis intextata
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Looks like T. mimela but I'm told more likely to be T. intextata which was seen flying on this night. At a sheet setup during a joint RCLandcare-Entomological Society night.
